olive oil
1 carrot
1 Kumara
2 potato
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
2 tbs plain flour
1 egg
1 packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet chicken breast
1 packet creamy pesto dressing

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut carrot, kumara and potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray and sprinkle over garlic & herb seasoning. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
• When the veggies are done, add baby leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Toss to combine and season to taste.

• Place chicken breast between two sheets of baking paper. Pound with a meat mallet or rolling pin until they are an even thickness, about 1cm.
• Meanwhile, combine the plain flour and a pinch of salt in a shallow bowl. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the egg. In a third shallow bowl, place panko breadcrumbs and Aussie spice blend.
• Coat chicken first in flour mixture, followed by the egg and finally the panko breadcrumbs. Transfer to a plate.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base.
• When oil is hot, cook crumbed chicken in batches until golden and cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.
TIP: Ensure the oil is hot before cooking the chicken schnitzels for best results.

• Slice chicken.
• Divide spiced roast veggies between plates. Top with crumbed chicken.
• Drizzle over creamy pesto dressing to serve. Enjoy!